{
  "stem": "25639.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, I read Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But this was not only so for Jewish kids.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were Mormons.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was some Mormon kids who were-- who were also excused, and-- and there were some-- there was a Russian school that also taught the Russian language.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So some of the White Russians in the area sent their kids to Russian school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They-- they did not teach them religion, I don't think-- possibly the Greek Catholic religion, not the Roman Catholic, but the Greek Catholic religion.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were other-- other schools.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I think there were three schools all together, each taught a-- a different religious-- religion.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, my brothers were well prepared, much more so than the girls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they studied the Mishnah and the Gemara, and they knew exactly how to-- what every word meant that they read, whereas, I never had that opportunity.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, I was much younger than either of my four brothers were.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So consequently, I missed out on that, but that's something that I can do on my own here.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we-- for most-- for meat, we would have a-- a ritual slaughterer come to our town for cattle, to slaughter the cattle.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However-- and the chickens, the poultry, was also done by a shochet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A shochet is also a-- a ritual-- ritual slaughterer, but it takes special facilities to, apparently, slaughter a-- a larger animal, such as a cow or a calf.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there was plenty of kosher food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not until later did this become a problem.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After 1938, our shochet was taken away from us, I think, around-- around 1942, approximately.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- we were left without a shochet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so we would have to go eight kilometers into Beregszasz to-- to have our chickens slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
